<h1>Problem 564 - 2017 IMOSL, A5</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>An integer \(n \geq 3\) is given. We call an \(n\)-tuple of real numbers \((x_1, x_2, \dots, x_n)\) Shiny if for each permutation \(y_1, y_2, \dots, y_n\) of these numbers, we have
\[\sum \limits_{i=1}^{n-1} y_i y_{i+1} = y_1y_2 + y_2y_3 + y_3y_4 + \cdots + y_{n-1}y_n \geq -1.\]Find the largest constant \(K = K(n)\) such that
\[\sum \limits_{1 \leq i < j \leq n} x_i x_j \geq K\]holds for every Shiny \(n\)-tuple \((x_1, x_2, \dots, x_n)\).</p>
